-- Peru Stocks: Candente, Maple, IRL, Panoro, Relapasa
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-05-28T21:07:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/peru-stocks-candente-maple-irl-panoro-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of market close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose for a third session, gaining
0.5 percent to 20,849.26. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed
0.2 percent to 2,662.38.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, jumped 7.5 percent to 72 cents as copper
advanced in  London  and investors bet the company will take on a
partner, said Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa
SAB.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, rose 1.7 percent to 59 cents.  Refineria la Pampilla SA  (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of Repsol
YPF SA, climbed 2.4 percent to 86 centimos after crude gained
for a third day in electronic trading in  New York .  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, advanced 1 percent to $1.05.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. gold producer with a mine
in Peru, fell 1.3 percent to 78 cents after bullion rose in
London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
